{
  "text": "We observed that the trajectory beyond the aortic root dilates more progressively in patients with a history of aortic root replacement, as previously reported. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] The aortic dilation rate of the aortic trajectory beyond the aortic root may be enhanced by haemodynamic factors, altered wall mechanics, loss of the Windkessel effect with higher pulsatile forces acting onto the descending aorta, or clamping of the aorta during the operation. [CITATION_4] In summary, losartan treatment reduces aortic root dilation rate in adults with MFS with a number-needed-to-treat of 5.3 patients when comparing the percentage of patients with stable aortic root between both groups. Following prophylactic aortic root replacement, losartan treatment also has a beneficial effect on dilation rate in the aortic arch.",
  "correct_citation": {
